"title": "5604: walls",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5604: walls",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Kinds of wall</h2>\n<h3>Walls of houses and palaces</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:7\">LAM 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:10-1Sam18:11\">1SA 18:10–18:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:25\">1SA 20:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:2\">ISA 38:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:5\">DAN 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>Walls of towns</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:7\">2CH 14:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:4\">NUM 35:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:10\">1SA 31:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:24\">2SA 18:24</a></p>\n<h3>Walls of cities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:5\">DEU 3:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:17\">NEH 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:15\">JOS 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:5\">JOS 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:20\">JOS 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:1\">1KI 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:27\">2KI 3:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr27:3\">2CH 27:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:10\">PSA 55:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:12\">ISA 58:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:25\">ACT 9:25</a></p>\n<h3>Walls of the temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:27\">1KI 6:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:12\">1KI 7:12</a></p>\n<h3>Walls of vineyards</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33\">MAT 21:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:24-Num22:25\">NUM 22:24–22:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:12\">PSA 80:12</a></p>\n<h2>The fragility of walls</h2>\n<h3>Walls broken down by enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:52\">DEU 28:52</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:28\">PRO 25:28</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:15\">JER 50:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:15\">2SA 20:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:13\">2KI 14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:4\">2KI 25:4</a> <em>the fall of Jerusalem to the Babylonians</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:6\">2CH 26:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:19\">2CH 36:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:3\">NEH 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:40\">PSA 89:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:5\">ISA 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:5\">ISA 22:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:8\">LAM 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:4\">EZK 26:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:3\">AMO 4:3</a></p>\n<h3>Walls collapsing of their own accord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:13\">ISA 30:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:30\">1KI 20:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:3\">PSA 62:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:10-Ezek13:16\">EZK 13:10–13:16</a></p>\n<h2>The figurative use of walls</h2>\n<h3>Denoting protection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:4\">ISA 25:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:16\">1SA 25:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:9\">EZR 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:1\">ISA 26:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:5\">ZEC 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Denoting separation and impregnability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14\">EPH 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:11\">PRO 18:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:10\">ISA 59:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:18\">JER 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:30\">EZK 22:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:3\">ACT 23:3</a></p>\n<h2>The walls in the new Jerusalem</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:12-Rev21:19\">REV 21:12–21:19</a></p>",
